- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the computation of a relation on the edge set of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses special data structures to compute Partial Star Products in constant time, and also discusses linear and sublinear time algorithms for recognizing certain types of graph products. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper mentions the recognition of Cartesian graph bundles, which is a topic in computational geometry. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses the weak reconstruction of Cartesian products, which is a topic in game theory. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the recognition of certain types of graph products, which is relevant to the study of social and information networks.
